Symptoms of gastrointestinal upset can include:
1) Halitosis (bad breath);
2) Loss of appetite;
3) Gain of weight;
4) Heartburn;
5) Altered perception of taste;
6) Pressure pain during climb;
7) Desire for certain food types;
8) Gastric and duodenal ulcers;
9) Loss of weight.

Hyperventilation (nor required by physical need) can be caused by:
1. Pressure breathing;
2. Anxiety or fear;
3. Overstress;
4. Strong pain;
5. Jogging.
